Text: That's...the eleventh one!
Aggghh!
Is that it? What a bunch of weaklings.

True, they put up less resistance than I expected. 
Even I picked up on that.
...Wait, have I become invincible?!
Pride comes before a fall, Epsilon.
Ah...! Of course, Lady Alpha. I'll be careful.
E-Eek...!
Wh-Who the hell are you...?!
Th-There were...twelve of us!
And the three of you took us all out head-on...!

The Cult members who we previously massacred here
were all taken by surprise and assassinated.

They likely thought they had strength in their
numbers—how foolish.

Perhaps the Cult of Diablos is drowning in the
corruption of their own power after spending
too long in the darkness.
How the hell...do you know that name?!
Why wouldn't we, since we know about this place?

But of course, there are things we don't know about—
and you'll be the one to enlighten us.
Like hell I will... I'm not telling you anything!
I see...
Then we'll make you. Delta.
On it! Die!

Nooo! You're supposed to hurt him without killing
him!
Hurt him? You mean play with my prey?
As long as that means not killing him.

Sometimes I accidentally kill my prey when I play
with them.

Then make sure that it doesn't happen this time! Just
pretend you're holding a baby chick! Don't use too
much pressure!

But baby chicks die super easily, even if you don't
use pressure! I mean, c'mon, this guy even looks like
a baby chick.
Y-You monsters! How dare you toy with my life!

I doubt that's their intention—but if that's how you
see it, I'm fine with that.
Okay! Time to play!
Aaaagghh!!!
M-My arm! My aaaarm!
Geez, he really is a weakling.

Delta! You can't just inflict a fatal wound right off
the bat!
Losing an arm isn't gonna kill him right away.
Maybe not right away, but it will eventually!

Losing enough blood will kill any creature sooner or
later!
I had no idea! I've never fought that way!
Nghh...!
You may be able to save your other arm if you talk.

O-Okay...alright! I'll talk! I'll talk... Just keep
that monster away from me!
...Delta. Stay.
Erk!
Okay.
You really are obedient when it comes to Lady Alpha.

Course I am. Lady Alpha is second in command after
Boss man. You don't even know that, Epsilon?
Of course I do...

This a way station for rounding up and transporting
the possessed in Lindwurm, isn't it?

Y-Yes! I've heard them refer to the possessed as
their precious "ingredient"...!
Their ingredient...!

They didn't tell us anything more! I mean it...
You've gotta believe me...aghh...!
Lady Alpha—

Looks like the Cult is keeping their cards close to
their chest—they're preventing leaks of sensitive
intel by only informing their underlings the bare
minimum.

And do you know anything about the paladin in the
strange mask?
Erk!
N-Not a clue...!

Are you sure? We know the Cult is rounding up the
possessed in the name of the Church.

Besides, we've already confirmed that the enemy we're
looking to lure out has been investigating Lindwurm's
underground ventilation system.

It seems they didn't train you to maintain your
composure while lying in a state of severe injury.
Ngh...!
If you know, then speak up! Or else you die now!

F-Fine! Alright! I'll talk! Just don't kill me,
please...!

Heh... Delta's simple "negotiation" tactics can be
highly effective when carried out correctly.
So? Who was the masked paladin?
Th-They're...templars...
Tempura?!

We're under a different chain of command. They answer
to the Church—
Oh! Lady Alpha!
Delta, get down!
Gah?!
Aaag...ghh...hhh...!
Chhhh...kuhhh...

They shot the Cult member down from that distance
with no hesitation! Was it to silence him?!
So...these are the templars!
Yup, "tempura"... Boss man told me about them before.
Shadow mentioned them?

You mean...he already knew the enemy's identity
before us?!
...Kuhhh...chhhh...

Delta, I have more questions for you, but I'll ask
them later.

First, we'll need to take care of these masked
paladins—
You will fall to my sword!
